ps between preservation, production, and redaction to shed light on the dark valley attributed to wartime culture and to cast a shadow on the supposedly bright, open space of free postwar discourse. (Winner of the 2010-2011 First Book Award of the Weatherhead East Asian Institute, Columbia University" ).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCensorshipzJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aExpurgated bookszJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aJapanese literaturexCensorshipxHistoryy20th century. 0aProhibited bookszJapanxHistoryy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  a20th century japan.  aanthropology.  aasian history.  abooks for history lovers.  acensorship japan.  acensorship system.  acensorship.  adiscussion books.  aeast asia.  ahomeschool history books.  ajapanese culture.  ajapanese economy.  ajapanese empire.  ajapanese history.  ajapanese imperialism.  ajapanese isolation.  ajapanese markets.  alearning while reading.  aleisure reads.  alife during war.  anonfiction books.  apass on books.  apassion reads.  apostwar discourse.  aquarantine books.  arise of modern japan.  awartime culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095340640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953406423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520953406/original  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles